cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.PL

The paper involves the integration of deep learning and model predictive control for self-tuning a mode-locked fiber laser. This work involves the development of intelligent algorithms capable of inferring approximate models of the underlying physics and discovering appropriate control laws. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of control theory and optimization techniques for maintaining robust performance, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques for analyzing the laser output, which suggests the category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of neural networks for approximating the unknown fiber birefringence, which suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the development of programming languages and software tools for implementing the proposed algorithmic architecture, which suggests the category cs.PL (Programming Languages).
